<TITLE> Police nabs man for harassing DU student </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 19 (bdnews24.com)  Police has arrested one Fuad Ahmed Babu, for harassing a female student of Dhaka University near Rokeya Hall. Babu, along with two of his friends, harassed a student of the university when she was on her way to the women's dorm, where she stays. The three men were located close to the Rokeya Hall with two motorcycles, at around 9.30pm. The DU student was hastening to her dorm since the dorm closes its doors at 9.30pm. Hearing abusive language directed towards her, the DU student protested and slapped Babu. This altercation managed to rouse the attention of others around the scene and 10 to 12 students came to her rescue. They beat up all three of the men, two of whom managed to flee. But the 22 year old Babu, a trader from Old Dhaka, could not. In the meantime, the university's proctor arrived at the scene and handed over Babu to the Shahbagh police. OC of Shahbagh Police Station, Rezaul Karim told bdnews24.com that the detained youth would be sent to court in the morning. Both their motorcycles are in police custody. bdn
